title: Zelensky confirms new Canadian aid package after talks with European leaders

author: Neal McCluskey and Kayla Susalla, opinion contributors
description: President Trump's plan to allow 600,000 Chinese students to study at U.S. universities could generate $43 billion for the U.S. economy, while a 17 percent decline in international student enrollment could cost the U.S. economy $18 billion and widen the existing gap in STEM talent.
title: International students are good for America

title: Newsom has strong year in California, but is he peaking too soon?
